@startuml
title AI Inspection Runtime Flow (As-Is)
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam linetype ortho

actor User
participant "Frontend Scanner\n(React)" as FE
participant "Backend API\nPOST /api/scans/quick-analyze" as API
participant "Standards Engine\n(evaluate_freshness_with_standards)" as Standards
participant "Visual Engine\n(evaluate_visual_spoilage)" as Visual
participant "Mock Engine\nmodel_inference_mock_v1" as Mock
database "Prometheus Counter\nfreshfood_scan_events_total" as Metric
database "ScanFeedbackEvent table" as FeedbackDB

User -> FE: Upload image / select profile
FE -> API: quick-analyze(image_file|image_url,\ncommodity_group, spoilage_profile, ref mm/px)

API -> Standards: Try standards-based scoring
alt standards_result != null
  Standards --> API: assessment_basis=standards_*
else standards null
  API -> Visual: Try visual spoilage quantification
  alt visual_result != null
    Visual --> API: assessment_basis=visual_spoilage_quantification_v2
  else visual null
    API -> Mock: fallback
    Mock --> API: assessment_basis=model_inference_mock_v1
  end
end

API -> Metric: record_scan_event(outcome=completed,\nassessment_basis=...)
API --> FE: freshness_level, confidence,\nspoilage_ratio_pct, needs_manual_review

alt Backend quick-analyze error
  FE -> FE: fallback local TFJS inference
end

User -> FE: Gui feedback dung/sai
FE -> FeedbackDB: POST /api/scans/feedback-events

note right of API
As-is:
- quick-analyze khong can auth
- quick-analyze khong persist scan history
end note

@enduml
